Cumae did not then possess the Roman franchise.

	<DIV CLASS="mynote">
	<P CLASS="b0 a0">
Thayer's Note: Prof. Falconer is too close to his subject, and the connection will mystify some. Towns, subject states, and even independent nations could be the client of a Roman patron, thus securing for themselves protection that the strict application of Roman law would not provide. See the article
	<A CLASS="smallcaps" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/secondary/SMIGRA*/Cliens.html#corporate_clients
