onMouseOut="nd();">Seneca, <I>De benef.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.10.4
	</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">haec enim beneficii inter duos lex est; alter statim oblivisci dati, alter accepti nunquam</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note55" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref55
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">55</A>
<I>i.e.</I> only by forming friendships when we are mature in mind and in age.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note56" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref56
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">56</A>
<I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#real_friendships_are_eternal
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">§ 32
	</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">verae amicitiae sempiternae sunt</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note57" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref57
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">57</A>
He won his election over Laelius by pretending that he was not a candidate, thus throwing Laelius off his guard.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note58" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref58
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">58</A>
From Theophrastus, <I>Περὶ φιλίας</I>: <SPAN LANG="el" CLASS="Greek">τοὺς ἀλλοτρίους οὐ φιλοῦντα δεῖ κρίνειν, ἀλλὰ κρίναντα φιλεῖν</SPAN>. Seneca also (<I>Ep.</I> <SPAN CLASS="small">III</SPAN>) quotes the maxim, and describes those neglecting it as acting <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">praepostere</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note59" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref59
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">59</A>
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/ter.andria.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Terence\'s Andria'+Lat2+LatSearch+'obsequium</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Terence, <I>Andria</I>, <SPAN CLASS="small">I</SPAN>.1.41</A>: <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">obsequium</SPAN> is chiefly used in a good sense, = the desire to oblige, or fall in with another's taste; but often, as here, it is almost "flattery."


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note60" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref60
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">60</A>
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/ter.eunuchus.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Terence\'s Eunuch'+Lat2+LatSearch+'negat quis</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Terent. <I>Eunuchus</I>, <SPAN CLASS="small">II</SPAN>.2.21 (l. 250)</A>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note61" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref61
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">61</A>
See §§ <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#37
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">37
	</A>
and <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#41
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">41</A>. The bill referred to was proposed by him in 130 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>, and failed to pass, but at some time after the time of this dialogue (129) was again offered and carried.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note62" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref62
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">62</A>
<I>i.e.</I> merely one of them; he was at the time a private citizen.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note63" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref63
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">63</A>
<I>i.e.</I> in 145 <SPAN CLASS="small">B.C.</SPAN>


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note64" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref64
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">64</A>
Plutarch,
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Caius_Gracchus*.html#5.3
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
<I>Vit. Grac.</I> 5</A>, makes C. Gracchus the author of this practice.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note65" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref65
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">65</A>
Laelius has in mind Thraso in the <I>Eunuch</I> of Terence, for which
	<A HREF="
http://www.thelatinlibrary.com/ter.eunuchus.html
	"TARGET="offsite"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(EClickHere+'Terence\'s Eunuch'+Lat2+LatSearch+'magnas</SPAN>',WIDTH,195)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(<SPAN CLASS="small">III</SPAN>.1.1)</A><A CLASS="correction"
onMouseOver="return Ebox('The Loeb edition<BR>has '+BadF+'II.1.1'+CloseF+'',WIDTH,120)"
onMouseOut="nd();">º</A> the following line is taken, and Pyrgopolinices, the braggart soldier in Plautus's <I>Miles Gloriosus</I>. The disgust Laelius feels at the fawning of the parasite is relieved by the humour of the soldier.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note66" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref66
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">66</A>
Lines from the <I>Epiclerus</I> by Caecilius Statius. <I>Cf.</I> <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Cato_Maior_de_Senectute/text*.html#36
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,0,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">Cic. <I>Cato Maior</I> § 36
	</A>
<SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">nam quos ait Caecilius . . . comicos stultos senes</SPAN>.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note67" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Cicero/Laelius_de_Amicitia/text*.html#ref67
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">67</A>
<I>i.e.</I> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">amor</SPAN>, "love"; <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">amicitia</SPAN>, "friendship."



